            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>Let me show how the reasoning improvements map to specific agents. The general agent needs the full reasoning protocol because it handles everything. The basic agent needs output format and confidence scoring but not the full workbench. Data analyst needs sandbox error recovery since execute_code failures are the biggest failure mode. Coordinator needs delegation context so worker agents understand what's being asked. We also propose five new skill packs for reasoning — step planning, self-verification, uncertainty handling, error recovery, and output formatting. The clever part is that SkillResolver injects them dynamically based on query complexity. Simple questions don't trigger the full scaffold. Complex multi-step tasks do. All just markdown files using existing infrastructure — no code changes.</a:t>
            </a:r>
